OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FCanada trials              
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fdecriminalising cocaine,   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5FMDMA and other drugs       
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Canada has announced it will           
OL,6, temporarily decriminalise the          
OL,7, possession of small amounts of some    
OL,8, illicit drugs in British Columbia (BC).
OL,10,FThe province asked for the criminal    
OL,11,Fcode exemption after overdoses claimed 
OL,12,Fmore than two thousand lives in BC last
OL,13,Fyear.                                  
OL,15,FThis time-limited three-year trial is  
OL,16,Fthe first of its kind in Canada.       
OL,18,FAdults will be allowed to possess a    
OL,19,Fcombined total of 2.5 grams of opioids,
OL,20,Fcocaine, methamphetamine and MDMA.     
